    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301852">Figure 52</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301852" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301852" filename="../figg13/g1301852.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and both countershaft rear bearing covers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301853">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301853" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301853" filename="../figg13/g1301853.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Remove Bolts and Countershaft Rear Bearing Covers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the groove at rear of each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301854">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301854" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301854" filename="../figg13/g1301854.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Remove Snap Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the countershafts forward and from the rear bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301855">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301855" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301855" filename="../figg13/g1301855.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Drive Countershafts Forward and From Rear Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, secure the assembly in a vise and remove the bearing inner race from the front
                of the countershaft with jaw pullers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301856">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301856" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301856" filename="../figg13/g1301856.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Remove Bearing Inner Race</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The vise used should be equipped with brass jaws or wood blocks to prevent damage to the
                        countershaft.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
